HEADWORD: Leaf-footed
<hw>Leaf"-foot`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having leaflike expansions on the legs; -- said of certain insects;
<as>as, the <ex>leaf-footed</ex> bug (<spn>Leptoglossus
phyllopus</spn>)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

